time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20deterioration%20took%20its%20toll.%20%26quot%3BThe%20morale%20of%20the%20whole%20store%20was%20basically%20terrible%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20When%20he%20started%2C%20people%20rarely%20talked%20about%20leaving.%20By%20last%20year%2C%20the%20most%20common%20topic%20he%20and%20his%20coworkers%20discussed%20was%20how%20much%20they%20wished%20they%20could%20quit.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20just%20getting%20worse%20and%20worse%20and%20worse.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchneider%20was%20witnessing%20Chipotle%20making%20a%20sharp%20U-turn.%20Founded%20in%201993%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchipotles-steve-ells-eyes-tiny-restaurant-with-robots-three-humans-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESteve%20Ells%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20former%20sous%20chef%20at%20a%20San%20Francisco%20fine%20dining%20pioneer%2C%20Chipotle%20became%20an%20elevated%20fast%20food%20juggernaut%20with%20more%20than%203%2C700%20locations%20around%20the%20world%2C%20going%20public%20in%202006.%20But%20the%20company%20suffered%20a%20series%20of%20food-borne%20illness%20outbreaks%20starting%20in%202015%2C%20when%2060%20people%20were%20sickened%20across%20nearly%20a%20dozen%20states.%20All%20restaurants%20closed%20for%20half%20a%20day%20in%20February%202016%20to%20deal%20with%20food%20safety.%20Then%20another%20norovirus%20outbreak%20hit%20in%202017.%20Ells%20stepped%20down%20as%20CEO%20a%20few%20months%20later%2C%20and%20he%20was%20replaced%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrian-niccols-career-taco-bell-chipotle-starbucks-ceo-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBrian%20Niccol%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20had%20just%20served%20as%20CEO%20of%20Taco%20Bell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222506%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Steve%20Ells%20and%20Brian%20Niccol%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68376ec4c6ad288d14821c44%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221671%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESteve%20Ells%2C%20a%20former%20sous%20chef%2C%20founded%20Chipotle%20in%201993%20and%20ran%20the%20company%20until%202018.%20His%20successor%2C%20Brian%20Niccol%2C%20had%20previously%20served%20as%20CEO%20of%20Taco%20Bell.%3Cp%3EGlen%20Martin%2FThe%20Denver%20Post%20via%20Getty%20Images%3B%20Robin%20Marchant%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENiccol%20led%20a%20dramatic%20turnaround.%20The%20efficiency-focused%20changes%20he%20put%20in%20place%20%E2%80%94%20including%20order%20screens%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchiptole-ceo-brian-niccol-talks-delivery-profits-and-digital-dominance-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edelivery%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%26quot%3BChipotlanes%26quot%3B%20drive-throughs%20%E2%80%94%20helped%20the%20company's%20annual%20revenue%20surge%20from%20%244.9%20billion%20in%202018%20to%20%2411.3%20billion%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20stock%20jumped%20tenfold%2C%20from%20%246%20a%20share%20in%20early%202018%20to%20more%20than%20%2460%20when%20Niccol%20left%20in%20mid-2024%20while%20its%20market%20cap%20grew%20from%20%249%20billion%20to%20more%20than%20%2480%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20happy%20as%20these%20changes%20made%20shareholders%2C%20the%20change%20in%20culture%20has%20been%20much%20more%20than%20a%20vibe%20shift%20for%20the%20company's%20130%2C000%20employees.%20Current%20and%20former%20employees%20say%20that%20Chipotle%20was%20once%20a%20special%20place%20to%20work%20%E2%80%94%20a%20cut%20above%20in%20fast%20casual%20dining%20%E2%80%94%20that%20has%20since%20been%20consumed%20by%20a%20fast%20food%20ethos%20that%2C%20for%20its%20workers%2C%20has%20made%20its%20restaurants%20barely%20distinguishable%20from%20a%20Burger%20King%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdomios-using-ai-make-ordering-from-a-bot-feel-real-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDomino's%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20evidence%20of%20a%20downgrade%20for%20staff%20has%20been%20popping%20up%20around%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20Chipotle%20agreed%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchipotle-to-pay-workers-20-million-over-labor-violations-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2420%20million%20settlement%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20New%20York%20City%20over%20claims%20of%20599%2C693%20violations%20of%20the%20city's%20scheduling%20and%20paid%20leave%20laws%2C%20more%20than%20any%20company%20has%20paid%20in%20a%20worker%20protection%20settlement%20in%20the%20city's%20history.%20In%202024%2C%20the%20company%20appeared%20in%20the%20second-place%20spot%2C%20behind%20Amazon%2C%20on%20the%20New%20York%20City%20Comptroller's%20%26quot%3BEmployer%20Wall%20of%20Shame%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcomptroller.nyc.gov%2Fservices%2Ffor-the-public%2Femployer-violations-dashboard%2Femployer-wall-of-shame%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estill%20appears%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Chipotle%20also%20agreed%20last%20year%20to%20pay%20%242.9%20million%20to%20Seattle-based%20employees%20in%20a%20settlement%20over%20allegations%20of%20failing%20to%20give%20extra%20pay%20for%20schedule%20changes%20and%20retaliating%20against%20employees%20who%20didn't%20take%20shifts%20they%20hadn't%20been%20scheduled%20for%20%E2%80%94%20the%20largest%20settlement%20the%20city%20had%20reached%20since%20its%20scheduling%20law%20took%20effect.%20That%20same%20year%2C%20a%20study%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nrn.com%2Fquick-service%2Fchipotle-starbucks-workers-are-citing-burnout-why-%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGlassdoor%20reviews%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20more%20than%20550%20of%20America's%20largest%20employers%20found%20that%20Chipotle%20had%20the%20second-highest%20rate%20of%20employee%20burnout%20(behind%20Progressive%20insurance).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Chipotle's%20chief%20corporate%20affairs%20officer%20Laurie%20Schalow%20writes%2C%20%26quot%3BOur%20employees%20are%20our%20greatest%20priority%2C%20and%20we%20are%20committed%20to%20providing%20a%20best-in-class%20work%20experience%20that%20includes%20robust%20training%20and%20development%20programs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20spoke%20with%20eight%20current%20and%20former%20Chipotle%20employees%20in%20four%20states%20whose%20tenures%20span%20from%202012%20to%20the%20present%3B%20four%20of%20them%20have%20been%20involved%20in%20union%20organization%20efforts.%20Each%20told%20the%20same%20story%2C%20resonant%20with%20the%20broader%20allegations%20and%20superlatives%3A%20Many%20of%20the%20qualities%20that%20made%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchipotle-making-it-mandatory-for-staff-to-smile-at-customers-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChipotle%20stand%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20an%20employer%20%E2%80%94%20offering%20a%20stellar%20working%20experience%20where%20they%20were%20well-trained%20and%20valued%20and%20able%20to%20offer%20customers%20a%20high-quality%20experience%20%E2%80%94%20have%20precipitously%20declined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20fast%20food%20brand%2C%20Chipotle%20has%20lofty%20values.%20%26quot%3BOur%20purpose%20is%20to%20cultivate%20a%20better%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20its%20website%20states.%20It%20has%20long%20prided%20itself%20on%20offering%20only%20fresh%20food%20%E2%80%94%20it%20doesn't%20have%20freezers%20at%20its%20restaurants%2C%20a%20rarity%20in%20an%20industry%20where%20the%20majority%20of%20ingredients%20are%20frozen.%20It%20also%20makes%20promises%20to%20its%20employees.%20%26quot%3BBeing%20real%20means%20treating%20our%20people%20right%2C%26quot%3B%20reads%20the%20company's%20mission%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChipotle%20brands%20themselves%20as%20the%20cool%20fast%20food%20place%20to%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Quinlan%20Muller%2C%20who%20started%20working%20at%20the%20Lawrence%2C%20Kansas%2C%20location%20with%20Schneider%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20pays%20better%20than%20many%20of%20its%20competitors%3A%20According%20to%20survey%20data%20from%20the%20Shift%20Project%2C%20a%20research%20venture%20from%20Harvard's%20Kennedy%20School%20and%20UC%20San%20Francisco%20that%20tracks%20low-wage%20workers%20over%20time%2C%20Chipotle%20employees%20report%20earning%20%2416%20an%20hour%20on%20average%20nationwide%2C%20while%20Burger%20King%20and%20Domino's%20pay%20%2414.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArrow%20Smith%20took%20a%20job%20at%20the%20Augusta%2C%20Maine%2C%20franchise%20a%20few%20years%20ago%20because%20a%20previous%20job%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdollar-general-sales-are-climbing-higher-income-shoppers-seek-deals-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDollar%20General%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3Bwasn't%20paying%20me%20enough%20to%20survive%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20they%20could%20make%20a%20dollar%20or%20two%20more%20per%20hour%20at%20Chipotle%2C%20plus%20tips.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnna%20started%20out%20at%20minimum%20wage%20at%20a%20location%20in%20Ohio%20in%202012%2C%20but%20quickly%20was%20making%20over%20%2460%2C000%20a%20year%20between%20raises%20and%20regular%20bonuses%20for%20exceeding%20sales%20metrics.%20She%20says%20she%20also%20got%20%26quot%3Bexcellent%26quot%3B%20health%20and%20dental%20benefits.%20She%20made%20more%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20than%20she%20does%20now%20in%20a%20marketing%20job.%20(She%20asked%20Business%20Insider%20to%20use%20a%20pseudonym%20because%20her%20husband%20still%20works%20at%20Chipotle.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223348%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Chipotle%20advertises%20hiring.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68376b10ca50259add4d3d22%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222232%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFor%20a%20fast%20food%20brand%2C%20Chipotle%20has%20lofty%20values.%20%26quot%3BOur%20purpose%20is%20to%20cultivate%20a%20better%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20its%20website%20states.%3Cp%3EBrian%20Snyder%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20higher%20pay%20came%20higher%20expectations.%20%26quot%3BYou%20had%20to%20be%20near%20perfect%20on%20everything%2C%26quot%3B%20Anna%20says.%20If%20she%20prepped%20produce%20that%20wasn't%20cut%20to%20the%20right%20size%2C%20it%20would%20get%20thrown%20out%2C%20and%20she%20would%20start%20over.%20%26quot%3BI%20never%20worked%20for%20a%20fast%20casual%20or%20fast%20food%20restaurant%20that%20had%20such%20a%20high%20level%20of%20standards%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20great%20environment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20standards%2C%20the%20people%20Business%20Insider%20spoke%20with%20say%2C%20were%20upheld%20by%20a%20rigorous%20training%20program%20that%20looked%20more%20like%20those%20at%20the%20Culinary%20Institute%20of%20America%2C%20Ells'%20alma%20mater%2C%20than%20what%20is%20typical%20in%20the%20fast%20food%20industry.%20Muller%20came%20into%20her%20job%20at%20Chipotle%20fresh%20off%20a%20short%20stint%20at%20another%20fast%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffast-food-chains-ai-supply-chain-efficiency-mcdonalds-taco-bell-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efood%20company%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20the%20training%20barely%20existed.%20At%20Chipotle%2C%20she%20was%20able%20to%20get%20trained%20in%20lots%20of%20different%20positions.%20%26quot%3BIt%20felt%20more%20fulfilling%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20new%20hire%20started%20out%20by%20watching%20training%20videos%20for%20each%20position%20and%20looking%20through%20booklets%20that%20broke%20down%20every%20minute%20aspect%20of%20the%20job.%20Then%20workers%20would%20watch%20other%20people%20do%20the%20tasks%20before%20doing%20the%20tasks%20themselves%20with%20a%20trainer%20to%20offer%20feedback.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20really%20in-depth%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Brandi%20McNease%2C%20who%20started%20as%20a%20crew%20member%20at%20a%20location%20in%20Augusta%2C%20Maine%20in%202016.%20Workers%20were%20trained%20for%20multiple%20positions%2C%20from%20manning%20the%20tortilla%20press%20to%20grilling%20the%20food%20in%20the%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20training%20also%20had%20a%20built-in%20progression%20to%20help%20people%20move%20from%20crew%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fex-middle-manager-big-tech-flattening-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emanagers%20and%20above%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThey%20wanted%20to%20grow%20people%20and%20bring%20them%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20McNease%20says.%20Smiling%20Estrella%2C%20who%20started%20working%20at%20a%20New%20York%20City%20Chipotle%20in%202016%2C%20was%20promoted%20from%20crew%20to%20kitchen%20leader%20within%20three%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20first%20food-borne%20illness%20outbreaks%2C%20sales%20volumes%20and%20the%20company's%20stock%20plummeted.%20Ells%20left%20his%20perch%20as%20CEO%20to%20find%20someone%2C%20he%20said%20at%20the%20time%2C%20who%20could%20help%20the%20company%20%26quot%3Bexecute%20better%20to%20ensure%20our%20future%20success.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarbucks-ceo-brian-niccol-changes-6-months-in-pulse-check-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBrian%20Niccol%3C%2Fa%3E%20espoused%20a%20fast-food%20mindset%20that%20Chipotle%20had%20previously%20eschewed.%20%26quot%3BHis%20experience%20and%20worldview%20is%20processed%2C%20profitable%2C%20and%20not%20very%20organic%20foods%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Michael%20W.%20Morris%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Columbia%20Business%20School.%20%26quot%3BHe's%20an%20MBA%20quantitative%20marketing%20kind%20of%20guy%2C%20good%20at%20cutting%20costs%20in%20supply%20chains.%26quot%3B%20Niccol%20brought%20in%20executives%20from%20Bloomin'%20Brands%2C%20which%20owns%20fast%20casuals%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foutback-steakhouse-bloomin-brands-hiring-workers-is-easy-sales-strong-2021-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOutback%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Carrabba's%2C%20and%20Panda%20Restaurant%20Group%2C%20the%20owner%20of%20Panda%20Express.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENiccol%20left%20Chipotle%20last%20summer%20to%20become%20CEO%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquitting-starbucks-5-step-process-save-thousands-annually-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStarbucks%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Chipotle's%20new%20CEO%20is%20cut%20from%20the%20same%20cloth%3A%20Scott%20Boatwright%2C%20who%20joined%20in%202017%2C%20had%20spent%20the%20previous%2018%20years%20at%20Arby's.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chipotle%20mobile%20order%20pickup%20sign.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68376b896ffb6822ec61aeae%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECEO%20Brian%20Niccol%20espoused%20a%20fast-food%20mindset%20that%20Chipotle%20had%20previously%20eschewed%2C%20adding%20things%20like%20LCD%20screens%20and%20%26quot%3BChipotlanes%26quot%3B%20drive-throughs.%3Cp%3ECC%20Photo%20Labs%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20Ells'%20exit%20came%20a%20change%20in%20internal%20culture.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20have%20an%20organizational%20culture%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconvenience-stores-challenging-fast-food-restaurants-fresh-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efast%20food%20restaurant%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20maintain%20a%20brand%20image%20of%20an%20organic%2C%20sustainable%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20Morris%20says.%20It%20%26quot%3Bdoesn't%20allow%20for%20the%20craft%20feeling%20or%20for%20the%20people%20who%20are%20passionate%20about%20food%20to%20be%20displaying%20that%20passion.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChipotle%20says%20it%20still%20conducts%20intensive%20%26quot%3Breal%20culinary%20training.%26quot%3B%20In%20a%20video%20on%20its%20recruitment%20site%2C%20a%20worker%20named%20Ryan%20says%20that%20when%20he%20started%20there%2C%20%26quot%3Bthey%20had%20so%20many%20step-by-step%20processes%20on%20how%20to%20learn%20everything.%26quot%3B%20Schalow%20says%20in%20her%20statement%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20always%20had%20new%20worker%20training%2C%20and%20we%20continuously%20re-assess%20our%20training%20program%20and%20revise%20it%20as%20we%20deem%20appropriate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20of%20the%20workers%20Business%20Insider%20spoke%20to%20say%20that%20the%20company's%20training%20quality%20has%20dropped%20off.%20By%20the%20time%20Leslie%20(who%20asked%20that%20Business%20Insider%20use%20a%20pseudonym%3B%20she%20still%20works%20at%20Chipotle)%20started%20working%20at%20a%20New%20York%20City%20location%20in%202019%2C%20she%20didn't%20get%20to%20watch%20a%20video%20or%20receive%20any%20hands-on%20guidance%20before%20she%20was%20put%20to%20work%2C%20she%20says.%20For%20each%20task%2C%20she%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bthey%20would%20explain%20it%20maybe%20once%20and%20that's%20it.%26quot%3B%20She%20didn't%20know%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchipotle-qdoba-moes-burrito-bowl-which-is-best-review-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20to%20wrap%20burritos%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20four%20months%20and%20figured%20it%20out%20by%20asking%20people%20to%20help%20her%20and%20watching%20videos%20during%20her%20off%20hours%2C%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20Augusta%20store%2C%20McNease%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20pretty%20clear%20that%20what%20I%20had%20stepped%20into%20was%20a%20transition%20period%20that%20was%20not%20going%20in%20the%20right%20direction.%26quot%3B%20New%20hires%20started%20to%20be%20put%20on%20the%20floor%20with%20no%20training%2C%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt%20got%20to%20the%20point%20where%20you%20were%20lucky%20if%20you%20got%20to%20watch%20videos.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20was%20happening%20in%20Kansas%2C%20as%20new%20hires%20wouldn't%20know%20how%20to%20do%20important%20tasks%2C%20Muller%20says.%20Thomas%20started%20working%20at%20the%20same%20Chipotle%20in%202022%20(he%20also%20asked%20that%20I%20use%20a%20pseudonym).%20By%20the%20time%20he%20left%20in%20late%202023%2C%20he%20says%20he%20consistently%20had%20to%20correct%20employees%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-mcdonalds-can-recover-from-food-safety-crisis-e-coli-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efood%20safety%3C%2Fa%3E%20procedures.%20In%20her%20statement%2C%20Schalow%20says%20the%20company's%20current%20training%20program%20%26quot%3Bincludes%20food%20safety%20training%2C%20workplace%20and%20employment-related%20training%2C%20and%20a%20range%20of%20operational%20training%20for%20various%20roles.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225692%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Chipotle%20worker%20makes%20a%20quesadilla.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68376bf0ca50259add4d3d60%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223795%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELast%20year%2C%20after%20a%20chorus%20of%20customers%20accused%20the%20company%20of%20skimping%20on%20portions%2C%20a%20Wells%20Fargo%20analyst%20ordered%20and%20weighed%2075%20iterations%20of%20the%20same%20item%2C%20and%20found%20a%20lot%20of%20variation.%3Cp%3EShannon%20Stapleton%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Schneider%20first%20started%2C%20there%20was%20a%20strict%20rule%20enforced%20that%20no%20one%20under%2018%20could%20use%20a%20knife%3B%20later%20on%2C%20kids%20as%20young%20as%2016%20were%20doing%20that%20prep%20work%2C%20he%20says.%20Schalow%20says%20the%20company%20has%20%26quot%3Bpolicies%20and%20procedures%20that%20comply%20with%20state%20laws%20for%20the%20employment%20of%2016-%20and%2017-year-olds.%26quot%3B%20Thomas%20says%20the%20focus%20switched%20from%20creating%20high-quality%20food%20to%20drilling%20down%20on%20portions%20%E2%80%94%20not%20giving%20customers%20too%20much.%20Managers%20%26quot%3Breally%20started%20hammering%20that%20into%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployee%20scheduling%20has%20also%20been%20tumultuous.%20According%20to%20Shift%20Project%20data%2C%20three-quarters%20of%20Chipotle%20employees%20it%20surveyed%20say%20they%20get%20their%20schedules%20less%20than%20two%20weeks%20in%20advance.%20More%20than%20a%20third%20get%20their%20schedules%20with%20less%20than%20a%20week's%20notice.%20Shifts%20also%20move%20frequently%3A%20Three-quarters%20of%20Chipotle%20employees%20report%20having%20received%20a%20shift%20timing%20change%20in%20the%20previous%20month%3B%2022%25%20had%20a%20canceled%20shift.%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20employee%20scheduling%2C%20%26quot%3BChipotle%20is%20really%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20heap%26quot%3B%20of%20comparable%20restaurants%2C%20says%20Daniel%20Schneider%2C%20a%20principal%20investigator%20at%20The%20Shift%20Project.%20Kristen%20Harknett%2C%20another%20principal%20investigator%2C%20says%20that%20canceled%20shifts%20are%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20disruptive%2C%26quot%3B%20particularly%20for%20workers%20who%20show%20up%20to%20a%20shift%20only%20to%20be%20sent%20home%20without%20receiving%20any%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Kansas%2C%20managers%20put%20up%20a%20printed%20schedule%20once%20a%20week%20on%20Saturday%20night%20or%20Sunday%2C%20say%20Schneider%20and%20Muller.%20There%20was%20no%20way%20to%20access%20it%20online%3B%20if%20someone%20didn't%20work%20that%20day%2C%20they%20might%20not%20know%20they%20were%20supposed%20to%20show%20up%20the%20following%20one.%20At%20the%20Maine%20store%2C%20workers%20sometimes%20wouldn't%20have%20their%20schedules%20by%20Sunday%20and%20would%20be%20told%20to%20show%20up%20to%20whatever%20shifts%20they%20had%20been%20scheduled%20for%20the%20previous%20Monday%2C%20says%20McNease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20the%20workers%20Business%20Insider%20spoke%20to%20also%20say%20that%20staff%20was%20so%20lean%20that%20employees%20on%20any%20given%20shift%20weren't%20able%20to%20handle%20the%20crush%20of%20customers%2C%20and%20that%20many%20shifts%20were%20chaotic.%20At%20the%20Augusta%20Chipotle%2C%20Smith%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20went%20from%20awesome%20and%20well-staffed%20to%20a%20skeleton%20crew%20in%20like%20a%20month.%26quot%3B%20McNease%20says%20managers%20told%20workers%20to%20work%20more%20hours%20and%20take%20over%20more%20positions%20without%20extra%20pay.%20Prep%20tasks%20like%20chopping%20food%20with%20sharp%20knives%20were%20done%20by%20two%20people%20instead%20of%20six%2C%20she%20adds%2C%20leading%20to%20injuries.%20One%20coworker%20cut%20his%20fingers%20seven%20or%20eight%20times%20trying%20to%20cut%20meat%20fast%20enough%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20line%20of%20customers%2C%20Smith%20says.%20%26quot%3BEvery%20day%20felt%20like%20a%20new%20set%20of%20small%20catastrophes.%20We%20were%20begging%20for%20more%20staffing%2C%20more%20help%2C%20and%20they%20just%20wouldn't%20send%20us%20anybody.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcNease%20also%20says%20that%20food%20would%20get%20left%20out%20too%20long%20and%20dirty%20dishes%20piled%20up.%20At%20the%20Lawrence%20Chipotle%2C%20says%20Muller%2C%20there%20were%20shifts%20with%20one%20person%20working%20on%20the%20line%20in%20the%20front%20and%20a%20shift%20manager%20in%20the%20back%20cooking%20food.%20Sometimes%20the%20store%20would%20get%20so%20busy%20that%20no%20one%20would%20be%20able%20to%20properly%20wash%20dishes%20and%20bowls%20between%20uses.%20During%20the%20company's%20earnings%20call%20in%20April%202025%2C%20Boatwright%20noted%20that%20internal%20research%20had%20found%20that%20some%20restaurants%20were%20unclean%20during%20peak%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20line%20of%20customers%20stand%20behind%20the%20counter%20of%20a%20makeline%20for%20Chipotle.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F669c626680d4d5da13d5a2c4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222009%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%202016%2C%20Chipotle's%20employee%20turnover%20rate%20was%20130%25.%20By%202021%20it%20had%20swelled%20to%20194%25.%20It%20fell%20to%20131%25%20last%20year.%3Cp%3EJoe%20Raedle%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEmployees%20blame%20the%20hecticness%2C%20in%20part%2C%20on%20climbing%20turnover%20rates.%20In%202016%2C%20the%20rate%20was%20130%25%2C%20according%20to%20the%20company.%20By%202021%20it%20had%20swelled%20to%20194%25%2C%20meaning%20nearly%20twice%20as%20many%20people%20left%20as%20were%20employed%20there%20that%20year.%20Rates%20have%20fallen%20since%20then%2C%20clocking%20in%20at%20145%25%20in%202023%20and%20131%25%20last%20year.%20%26quot%3BWe%20firmly%20believe%20in%20consistent%20and%20predictable%20scheduling%20and%20providing%20our%20employees%20with%20sufficient%20advanced%20notice%20of%20their%20schedule%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Schalow.%20%26quot%3BOur%20staffing%20levels%20are%20the%20best%20they%20have%20been%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20and%20we%20continue%20to%20see%20record%20low%20turnover%20rates%20in%20our%20restaurants.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20issues%20have%20trickled%20down%20to%20customers%2C%20who%20workers%20say%20have%20had%20to%20wait%20in%20longer%20lines%20or%20forgo%20ingredients%20that%20couldn't%20be%20cooked%20and%20prepped%20in%20time.%20Last%20year%2C%20after%20a%20chorus%20of%20customers%20accused%20the%20company%20of%20skimping%20on%20portions%20on%20TikTok%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fwells-fargo-review%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWells%20Fargo%3C%2Fa%3E%20restaurant%20analyst%20ordered%20and%20weighed%2075%20iterations%20of%20the%20same%20item%20at%20eight%20locations%20across%20New%20York%20City%20%E2%80%94%20and%20found%20a%20lot%20of%20variation.%20Niccol%20denied%20there%20was%20any%20directive%20to%20offer%20smaller%20portions%2C%20and%20announced%20training%20to%20ensure%20consistent%20amounts%20across%20locations%20%E2%80%94%20although%20not%20before%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchipotle-making-it-mandatory-for-staff-to-smile-at-customers-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshareholder%20lawsuit%20over%20the%20matter%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20not%20changed%20our%20portion%20sizes%2C%20and%20we%20have%20reinforced%20proper%20portioning%20with%20our%20employees%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Schalow.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we%20did%20not%20deliver%20on%20our%20value%2C%20we%20want%20our%20guests%20to%20reach%20out%20so%20we%20can%20make%20it%20right.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223175%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20lone%20worker%20at%20Chipotle.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68376c996ffb6822ec61af07%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221788%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20response%20to%20portion-skimping%20allegations%2C%20customers%20have%20taken%20to%20filming%20workers%20as%20they%20make%20their%20burritos.%3Cp%3EAlexandra%20Buxbaum%2FSipa%20USA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20and%20more%20often%2C%20customers%20get%20nasty%20with%20employees.%20%26quot%3BWe'd%20get%20yelled%20at%2C%20screamed%20at%2C%26quot%3B%20Anna%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt%20got%20so%20much%20worse%20as%20the%20years%20went%20on.%26quot%3B%20In%20response%20to%20the%20portion-skimping%20allegations%2C%20customers%20have%20taken%20to%20filming%20workers%20as%20they%20make%20their%20burritos.%20It%20made%20employees%20%26quot%3Breally%20uncomfortable%20to%20have%20cameras%20in%20our%20faces%20while%20we%20were%20working%2C%26quot%3B%20Thomas%20says.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20were%20very%20rude%20about%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchalow%20at%20Chipotle%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20do%20not%20condone%20guests%20who%20mistreat%20our%20teams%20and%20fail%20to%20give%20them%20the%20respect%20they%20deserve.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20people%20would%20lash%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Smith.%20%26quot%3BIt%20got%20really%20dehumanizing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnna%2C%20who%20had%20at%20one%20time%20loved%20her%20job%20so%20much%20she%20planned%20to%20stay%20as%20long%20as%20she%20could%2C%20says%20that%20the%20job%20became%20so%20disorganized%20and%20overwhelming%20that%20she%20quit%20after%20eight%20years%20with%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20April's%20earnings%20call%2C%20Boatwright%20also%20noted%20that%20employees%20were%20%26quot%3Bnot%20as%20friendly%20as%20we%20probably%20should%20be%20in%20restaurant.%26quot%3B%20His%20solution%3A%20Urging%20them%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchipotle-making-it-mandatory-for-staff-to-smile-at-customers-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egreet%20customers%20with%20a%20friendly%20smile%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bsmiles%20down%20the%20line%20don't%20slow%20us%20down.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20years%2C%20a%20number%20of%20Chipotle%20workers%20around%20the%20country%20have%20decided%20to%20organize.%20In%20New%20York%2C%20Leslie%20was%20approached%20by%20SEIU%2032BJ%2C%20a%20union%20that%20organizes%20primarily%20low-wage%20workers%20like%20cleaners%20and%20food%20service%20workers.%20She%20had%20previously%20been%20in%20a%20union%20while%20working%20at%20a%20nursing%20home%2C%20and%20she%20liked%20the%20idea%20of%20having%20one%20at%20Chipotle%2C%20too.%20Chipotle%20did%20not%20agree%2C%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'll%20tell%20you%20one%20thing%2C%20Chipotle%20hates%20the%20union%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Smiling%20Estrella.%20After%20he%20was%20on%20the%20news%20for%20attending%20a%20protest%20in%20New%20York%2C%20Chipotle%20accused%20him%20of%20forcing%20someone%20to%20work%20during%20his%20unpaid%20break%20and%20making%20employees%20clock%20out%20before%20working%20to%20close%20up%20the%20store.%20He%20denies%20it%2C%20calling%20the%20accusations%20%26quot%3Blies.%26quot%3B%20In%20early%202023%2C%20he%20was%20fired.%20%26quot%3BThat%20was%20really%20freaking%20hard%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20went%20through%20a%20deep%20depression.%26quot%3B%20He%20nearly%20lost%20his%20apartment%20as%20he%20struggled%20to%20make%20rent%2C%20and%20his%20phone%20service%20was%20cut%20off%20twice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20Chipotle%20was%20hit%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcomptroller.nyc.gov%2Fservices%2Ffor-the-public%2Femployer-violations-dashboard%2Femployer-wall-of-shame%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseven%3C%2Fa%3E%20unfair%20labor%20practice%20charges%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20the%20most%20of%20any%20employer.%20There%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nlrb.gov%2Fsearch%2Fcase%2Fchipotle%3Ff%255b0%255d%3Dcase_type%3AC%26s%255b0%255d%3DOpen%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efour%20open%20charges%20%3C%2Fa%3Eagainst%20the%20company%20sitting%20with%20the%20federal%20National%20Labor%20Relations%20Board%20for%20alleged%20behavior%20such%20as%20unfairly%20disciplining%20and%20threatening%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225760%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Current%20and%20former%20Chipotle%20workers%20marching%20to%20demand%20%2420%2Fhour%20wages%20and%20fair%20workplace%20practices.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68376d07ca50259add4d3db8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%202023%2C%20Chipotle%20was%20hit%20by%20seven%20unfair%20labor%20practice%20charges%20in%20New%20York%20City.%3Cp%3EKarla%20Ann%20Cote%2FNurPhoto%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWorkers%20at%20a%20Michigan%20location%20prevailed%20in%20forming%20a%20union.%20In%202022%2C%20employees%20at%20a%20Chipotle%20in%20Lansing%20overwhelmingly%20voted%20to%20join%20the%20International%20Brotherhood%20of%20Teamsters%20to%20address%20what%20they%20said%20were%20similar%20issues%20of%20understaffing%20and%20inconsistent%20schedules.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjacobin.com%2F2022%2F09%2Fchipotle-workers-lansing-michigan-union-teamsters%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworkers%20say%3C%2Fa%3E%20they%20were%20barraged%20by%20captive-audience%20meetings%20and%20anti-union%20messaging%3B%20the%20NLRB%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nlrb.gov%2Fcase%2F07-CA-348753%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20company%20had%20violated%20labor%20law%20by%20trying%20to%20deny%20raises%20to%20the%20unionized%20workers.%20They%20are%2C%20to%20date%2C%20the%20only%20unionized%20location.%20More%20than%20two%20years%20later%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.marketplace.org%2Fstory%2F2024%2F12%2F04%2Fchipotle-workers-union-contract-boycott%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edon't%20have%20a%20contract%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20other%20union%20campaign%20has%20succeeded.%20In%20March%202022%2C%20the%20%26quot%3Bwheels%20started%20to%20fall%20off%26quot%3B%20at%20the%20Augusta%20location%2C%20McNease%20says.%20She%20had%20been%20trying%20to%20do%20training%20%26quot%3Bcorrectly%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20struggled%2C%20particularly%20as%20people%20kept%20quitting.%20A%20gas%20leak%20in%20the%20restaurant%20started%20making%20people%20sick%2C%20and%20it%20took%20the%20company%20weeks%20to%20send%20someone%20out%20to%20fix%20it%2C%20she%20says.%20That's%20when%20she%20got%20in%20touch%20with%20someone%20she%20knew%20who%20was%20in%20a%20union%20to%20find%20out%20more%20about%20the%20process.%20The%20first%20step%2C%20she%20was%20advised%2C%20was%20to%20talk%20to%20coworkers%20about%20forming%20a%20union.%20%26quot%3BIt%20immediately%20just%20took%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployees%20were%20primed%20for%20it.%20%26quot%3BWe%20were%20just%20tired%20of%20corporate%20not%20listening%20to%20us.%20We%20were%20literally%20begging%20for%20help%2C%26quot%3B%20Smith%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20June%2015%2C%20McNease%20sent%20an%20email%20on%20behalf%20of%20her%20coworkers%20to%20the%20restaurant's%20team%20director%2C%20laying%20out%20their%20demands.%20It%20said%20that%2C%20since%20the%20previous%20December%2C%20the%20store%20had%20gone%20without%20training%20for%20new%20or%20existing%20employees%2C%20that%20two%20workers%20had%20been%20%26quot%3Broutinely%20expected%26quot%3B%20to%20complete%20the%20prep%20tasks%20usually%20done%20by%20six%2C%20and%20that%20three%20or%20four%20people%20had%20to%20open%20the%20store%2C%20work%20that%20required%20seven%20people.%20These%20issues%20put%20not%20just%20employees%20but%20customers%20at%20risk%2C%20with%20food%20safety%20%26quot%3Bcompromised%2C%26quot%3B%20McNease%20wrote.%20If%20the%20company%20didn't%20schedule%20a%20%26quot%3Bfull%20crew%26quot%3B%20to%20open%20the%20store%20by%20the%20following%20morning%2C%20the%20letter%20said%2C%20they%20wouldn't%20show%20up%20to%20work%20until%20they%20had%20enough%20staff%20and%20training.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.centralmaine.com%2F2022%2F06%2F16%2Faugusta-chipotle-workers-walk-out-claim-unsafe-conditions-due-to-understaffing%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ekicked%20off%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20two-day%20walkout.%20Six%20days%20later%2C%20the%20workers%20became%20the%20first%20Chipotle%20location%20in%20the%20country%20to%20file%20for%20a%20union%20election%20with%20the%20NLRB.%20%26quot%3BManagement%20descended%20on%20us%20immediately%2C%26quot%3B%20McNease%20says.%20Employees%20were%20called%20into%20mandatory%20meetings%20that%20were%20filled%20with%20anti-union%20rhetoric.%20The%20company%20made%20new%20hires%20that%20diluted%20the%20organizing%20unit%2C%20McNease%20says%3B%20managers%20screamed%20at%20people%20and%20overloaded%20supporters%20with%20tasks.%20People%20were%20sent%20home%20for%20slight%20uniform%20infractions%20and%20fired%20for%20%26quot%3Bstupid%20reasons%2C%26quot%3B%20Smith%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20on%20the%20same%20morning%20that%20the%20workers%20had%20an%20NLRB%20hearing%20to%20set%20an%20election%20date%2C%20Chipotle%20sent%20employees%20notice%20that%20it%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mainepublic.org%2Fbusiness-and-economy%2F2022-07-19%2Fchipotle-closes-augusta-store-amid-workers-union-drive%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshutting%20the%20store%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%20permanently.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20like%20the%20rug%20had%20been%20pulled%20out%20from%20under%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20McNease%20says.%20Workers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wbur.org%2Fnews%2F2023%2F03%2F28%2Fchipotle-labor-union-settlement-augusta-maine%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esettled%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20company%2C%20receiving%20a%20total%20of%20%24240%2C000%20in%20back%20pay.%20%26quot%3BWe%20fought%20so%20hard%2C%26quot%3B%20McNease%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20in%20the%20end%2C%20they%20were%20able%20to%20just%20walk%20away.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20respect%20our%20employees'%20rights%20to%20organize%20under%20the%20National%20Labor%20Relations%20Act%20and%20are%20committed%20to%20ensuring%20a%20fair%2C%20just%20and%20humane%20work%20environment%20that%20provides%20opportunities%20to%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Schalow.%20%26quot%3BWe%20closed%20our%20Augusta%2C%20Maine%20restaurant%20because%20of%20location-specific%20staffing%20challenges%20of%20this%20fairly%20remote%20location%20and%20other%20issues%2C%20not%20because%20of%20any%20union%20activities%20of%20the%20employees%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuller%20started%20talking%20to%20her%20coworkers%20about%20unionizing%20around%20the%20time%20McNease's%20campaign%20faltered.%20She%20drew%20up%20a%20petition%20for%20the%20NLRB%20and%20quickly%20got%20most%20of%20her%20coworkers%20to%20sign.%20After%20management%20found%20out%20in%20October%202022%2C%20the%20company%20deployed%20similar%20tactics%20as%20those%20in%20Maine%2C%20she%20says.%20Higher-ups%20workers%20had%20never%20seen%20before%20showed%20up%2C%20employees%20say%2C%20pulling%20them%20into%20lengthy%20one-on-one%20meetings%20with%20anti-union%20talking%20points%3B%20employees%20felt%20they%20were%20disciplined%20or%20even%20fired%20for%20small%20things%20that%20had%20never%20previously%20raised%20alarm%20bells.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20December%2C%20one%20of%20Muller's%20friends%20came%20in%20for%20a%20burrito%20bowl%20and%20some%20chips%20in%20the%20evening%2C%20and%20Muller%20offered%20her%20the%20chips%20for%20free%20before%20they%20got%20thrown%20out%20for%20the%20day%2C%20a%20practice%20accepted%20by%20other%20managers%2C%20she%20says.%20Her%20manager%20wrote%20her%20up%2C%20and%20she%20was%20fired%20for%20stealing.%20It%20happened%20just%20days%20before%20a%20deadline%20to%20have%20Chipotle%20reimburse%20her%20tuition%20for%20the%20semester%2C%20costing%20her%20%242%2C600.%20She%20was%20unemployed%20for%20six%20months.%20It%20was%20also%20emotionally%20difficult%20to%20lose%20her%20job.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20kind%20of%20a%20part%20of%20my%20identity%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuller%20filed%20complaints%20with%20the%20NLRB%2C%20which%20later%20found%20that%20the%20restaurant%20had%20punished%20workers%20who%20were%20involved%20in%20unionizing%20and%20had%20tried%20to%20discourage%20the%20effort%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flawrencekstimes.com%2F2023%2F11%2F30%2Fdowntown-chipotle-ulp-settlement%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esettlement%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20required%20Chipotle%20to%20post%20a%20notice%20about%20workers'%20rights%20to%20organize.%20No%20one%20was%20reinstated%20or%20given%20back%20pay.%20The%20union%20campaign%20fizzled.%20%26quot%3BEveryone%20was%20scared%2C%26quot%3B%20Schneider%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%20a%20year%20into%20Boatwright's%20tenure%20as%20CEO%2C%20Chipotle%20keeps%20expanding%20%E2%80%94%20it%20plans%20to%20open%20more%20than%20300%20locations%20this%20year%20%E2%80%94%20though%20there%20are%20signs%20of%20trouble.%20The%20company's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchipotle-customers-eating-less-beef-going-for-chicken-instead-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esame-store%20sales%20have%20declined%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20two%20consecutive%20quarters%20in%202025%2C%20the%20first%20two%20quarterly%20drops%20since%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%20Chipotle's%20stock%20sits%20at%20%2441.44%2C%20down%2037%25%20from%20a%20high%20of%20%2466.16%20last%20December.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20more%20than%20seven%20years%20at%20Chipotle%2C%20Schneider%20left%20last%20year%20after%20he%20graduated%20from%20college.%20He%20even%20took%20a%20pay%20cut%20to%20take%20his%20new%20job%20as%20a%20graphic%20designer.%20But%20now%20he%20feels%20respected%20and%20valued%20as%20a%20member%20of%20a%20team%2C%20and%20the%20person%20above%20him%20treats%20him%20%26quot%3Blike%20a%20person.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20never%20been%20happier%2C%20honestly%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fbryce-covert%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBryce%20Covert%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20an%20independent%20journalist%20writing%20about%20the%20economy.%20She%20is%20a%20contributing%20op-ed%20writer%20at%20the%20New%20York%20Times%20and%20a%20contributing%20writer%20at%20The%20Nation.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchipotle-dream-gig-employees-burrito-blues-fast-food-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1754813461000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68376dca6ffb6822ec61af66%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchipotle-dream-gig-employees-burrito-blues-fast-food-2025-8%2