t%20them%20are%20early%20morning%20and%20late%20evening.%20When%20looking%20for%20scrapes%20or%20faeces%2C%20you%20can%20find%20them%20in%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20valley%20or%20along%20the%20ridgeline.%20They%20make%20a%20pile%20of%20sand%20with%20their%20hind%20legs%20sitting%20on%20the%20ground%20and%20then%20urinate%20atop%20it.%20This%20is%20how%20they%20mark%20territory.%20They%20also%20rub%20their%20necks%20or%20cheeks%20on%20hanging%20rocks%2C%20leaving%20behind%20fur.%20One%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20look%20for%20high%20hanging%20rocks%20but%20suitably%20sized%20ones%2C%20where%20they%20can%20stand%20up%20and%20rub%20their%20necks.%20Here%20they%20also%20urinate%20and%20spray%20a%20pungent%20liquid%20from%20scent%20glands%20located%20under%20the%20base%20of%20the%20tail.%20Each%20one%20has%20its%20own%20unique%20scent%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Khenrab.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%20wp-image-239891%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124938.437-1754570099.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22During%20his%20two-decade%20tenure%20as%20a%20wildlife%20guard%2C%20Khenrab%20has%20been%20involved%20in%20rescuing%2047%20snow%20leopards.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124938.437-1754570099.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124938.437-1754570099-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124938.437-1754570099-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124938.437-1754570099-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124938.437-1754570099-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-483421%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EDuring%20his%20two-decade%20tenure%20as%20a%20wildlife%20guard%2C%20Khenrab%20has%20been%20involved%20in%20rescuing%2047%20snow%20leopards.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20February-March%2C%20which%20is%20the%20mating%20season%20for%20the%20snow%20leopards%2C%20these%20hanging%20rocks%20are%20used%20frequently%20to%20scan%20and%20smell%20for%20potential%20mates.%20If%20these%20signs%20don%E2%80%99t%20work%2C%20they%20start%20calling%20each%20other%20on%20top%20of%20these%20ridgelines%20since%20this%20is%20the%20quickest%20way%20to%20communicate.%20Once%20you%20know%20where%20to%20look%2C%20the%20likelihood%20of%20spotting%20a%20snow%20leopard%20directly%20through%20your%20binoculars%20increases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ERescuing%20snow%20leopards%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20late%201970s%20and%2080s%2C%20some%20snow%20leopards%20were%20killed%20by%20the%20local%20populace%20in%20retaliation%20for%20their%20attacks%20on%20livestock.%20These%20predators%20would%20enter%20various%20corral%20pens%20in%20villages%20and%20kill%20livestock%2C%20a%20major%20source%20of%20income%20for%20many%20families.%20When%20snow%20leopards%20get%20sick%2C%20old%20or%20can%E2%80%99t%20hunt%20in%20the%20wild%2C%20they%20target%20livestock%20in%20corral%20pens%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20kills%20have%20significantly%20reduced%20since%20then%20because%20of%20awareness%20raised%20by%20the%20Wildlife%20Protection%20Department%20and%20other%20government%20agencies%20about%20the%20legal%20penalties%20involved%20for%20killing%20snow%20leopards%2C%20including%20jail%20time.%20Today%2C%20whenever%20a%20snow%20leopard%20enters%20a%20human%20habitation%2C%20the%20people%20immediately%20call%20the%20rescue%20team%20of%20the%20Wildlife%20Protection%20Department.%20After%20it%E2%80%99s%20in%20the%20safe%20hands%20of%20the%20rescue%20team%2C%20a%20vet%20assesses%20its%20medical%20condition.%20Once%20the%20snow%20leopard%20is%20deemed%20medically%20fit%2C%20it%20is%20let%20back%20into%20the%20wild.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%20wp-image-239905%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124858.341-1754570447.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22With%20modern%20techniques%2C%20it's%20critical%20to%20understand%20how%20much%20of%20a%20drug%20needs%20to%20be%20used%20in%20a%20dart%20before%20tranquillizing%20the%20snow%20leopard%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124858.341-1754570447.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124858.341-1754570447-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124858.341-1754570447-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124858.341-1754570447-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124858.341-1754570447-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-483425%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EWith%20modern%20techniques%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20critical%20to%20understand%20how%20much%20of%20a%20drug%20needs%20to%20be%20used%20in%20a%20dart%20before%20tranquillising%20the%20snow%20leopard%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFrom%202000%20onwards%2C%20the%20introduction%20of%20ecotourism%2C%20particularly%20in%20villages%20in%20the%20vicinity%20of%20areas%20like%20the%20Hemis%20National%20Park%2C%20played%20a%20big%20part%20in%20furthering%20the%20change%20in%20mindset%20against%20killing%20these%20predators.%20When%20tourists%20began%20visiting%20villages%20like%20Chilling%20to%20spot%20snow%20leopards%20and%20live%20in%20local%20homestays%2C%20the%20villagers%20began%20to%20earn%20enough%20to%20offset%20any%20livestock%20loss%20to%20the%20predator.%20Along%20with%20my%20colleagues%20Smanla%20Tsering%20and%20Tsering%20Tashi%2C%20I%20was%20involved%20in%20training%20local%20eco-guides%2C%20who%20ensured%20tourists%20kept%20the%20premises%20clean%2C%20facilitated%20their%20interaction%20with%20homestay%20owners%2C%20and%20knew%20where%20to%20take%20them%20to%20spot%20these%20creatures%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Khenrab.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20process%20of%20rescuing%20snow%20leopards%20is%20a%20hard%20job%20with%20lots%20of%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20I%20began%20my%20work%20rescuing%20these%20predators%20in%201995%2C%20we%20had%20no%20equipment.%20We%20would%20merely%20carry%20empty%20gunny%20sacks%2C%20ropes%20and%20sticks%20for%20these%20rescue%20missions%20in%20different%20villages%20where%20snow%20leopards%20were%20stuck%20inside%20corral%20pens.%20It%20was%20extremely%20risky%20work.%20One%20of%20my%20senior%20colleagues%20nearly%20had%20his%20entire%20hand%20bitten%20off%20during%20one%20such%20rescue%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Tsering%20Tashi%2C%20a%20range%20officer%20posted%20in%20Changthang.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20his%20two-decade%20tenure%20as%20a%20wildlife%20guard%2C%20Khenrab%20has%20been%20involved%20in%20rescuing%2047%20snow%20leopards.%20And%20in%20the%20early%20days%2C%20these%20rescues%20were%20conducted%20without%20tranquilisers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20first%20rescue%20mission%20with%20Khenrab%20was%20in%20Ney%20village%20sometime%20in%20the%20early%202000s.%20The%20snow%20leopard%20was%20caught%20inside%20a%20corral%20pen%20with%20multiple%20rooms%2C%20while%20villagers%20outside%20were%20standing%20around%20terrified.%20We%20noticed%20that%20the%20snow%20leopard%20was%20sitting%20near%20one%20of%20the%20windows.%20I%20explained%20to%20Khenrab%20that%20we%20must%20first%20close%20the%20window%20from%20outside.%20Once%20we%20closed%20the%20window%2C%20we%20drove%20the%20snow%20leopard%20into%20the%20last%20room%20of%20the%20corral%20pen.%20There%20was%20just%20one%20door.%20We%20had%20carried%20a%20blanket%20with%20us%20inside%20the%20corral%20pen%2C%20while%20an%20elaborate%20net%20trap%20set%20up%20at%20the%20door.%20Two%20others%20were%20standing%20guard%20outside%2C%E2%80%9D%20recalls%20Tashi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20they%20entered%20the%20room%20with%20a%20blanket%2C%20Tashi%20warned%20Khenrab%20not%20to%20run%20away%20if%20the%20snow%20leopard%20jumped%20on%20them%20because%20the%20animal%20was%20also%20scared%20for%20its%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSo%2C%20when%20we%20closed%20in%20on%20the%20snow%20leopard%2C%20it%20jumped%20towards%20us.%20We%20wrapped%20the%20snow%20leopard%20in%20our%20blanket%20first%20before%20driving%20it%20inside%20our%20net.%20Post-2000s%2C%20however%2C%20we%20started%20getting%20some%20equipment%20like%20camouflage%20nets%2C%20blowpipes%20and%20tranquilliser%20guns.%20Most%20of%20my%20rescues%20were%20without%20tranquillisers%20since%20possible%20overdoses%20can%20harm%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Tashi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%20wp-image-239913%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T125010.112-1754570516.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22After%20rescuing%20the%20snow%20leopard%2C%20they%20are%20released%20back%20into%20the%20wild.%20Both%20Khenrab%20and%20Smanla%20Tsering%20were%20awarded%20the%20Royal%20Bank%20of%20Scotland's%20%E2%80%9CSave%20the%20Species%20Award%E2%80%9D%20for%20their%20work%20on%20snow%20leopard%20conservation%20in%202017.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T125010.112-1754570516.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T125010.112-1754570516-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T125010.112-1754570516-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T125010.112-1754570516-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T125010.112-1754570516-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-483428%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAfter%20rescuing%20the%20snow%20leopard%2C%20they%20are%20released%20back%20into%20the%20wild.%20Both%20Khenrab%20and%20Smanla%20Tsering%20were%20awarded%20the%20Royal%20Bank%20of%20Scotland%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9CSave%20the%20Species%20Award%E2%80%9D%20for%20their%20work%20on%20snow%20leopard%20conservation%20in%202017.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWith%20modern%20techniques%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20critical%20to%20understand%20how%20much%20of%20a%20drug%20needs%20to%20be%20used%20in%20a%20dart%20before%20tranquillising%20the%20snow%20leopard.%20You%20have%20to%20assess%20the%20size%20of%20the%20animal%20before%20loading%20the%20darts%20with%20drugs.%20Also%2C%20you%20still%20have%20to%20be%20careful%20because%20it%E2%80%99s%20an%20aggressive%20animal.%20It%E2%80%99s%20very%20important%20not%20to%20get%20too%20close%20and%20also%20to%20prevent%20sudden%20movements%20and%20carefully%20calculate%20how%20to%20trap%20it.%20If%20you%20rush%20the%20process%2C%20the%20animal%20gets%20very%20aggressive%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Khenrab.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETashi%20goes%20on%20to%20add%2C%20%E2%80%9CKhenrab%20has%20a%20genuine%20love%20for%20snow%20leopards.%20Even%20if%20called%20upon%20for%20a%20rescue%20past%20midnight%2C%20he%20never%20shies%20away%20from%20taking%20up%20the%20assignment.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThreats%20remain%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvery%20year%2C%20about%2021%20to%2045%20snow%20leopards%20are%20killed%20in%20India%20for%20poaching%20or%20as%20retaliation%20for%20livestock%20loss%2C%20according%20to%20a%202016%20report%20by%20Traffic%2C%20a%20wildlife%20trade%20monitoring%20network.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20Ladakh%2C%20the%20biggest%20threat%20to%20their%20survival%20is%20habitat%20destruction%20due%20to%20rising%20urbanisation%20and%20development%20activities%20that%20are%20happening%20around%20villages%20and%20in%20areas%20where%20their%20prey%20feast.%20When%20massive%20areas%20are%20cordoned%20off%20for%20developmental%20activities%2C%20losing%20all%20the%20alpine%20plants%20and%20other%20scarce%20vegetation%20is%20detrimental%20to%20herbivorous%20animals%20like%20blue%20sheep%2C%20goats%2C%20marmots%2C%20etc.%20These%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20are%20food%20for%20snow%20leopards.%20Another%20threat%20is%20a%20scarcity%20of%20water%20as%20a%20result%20of%20fast-shrinking%20glaciers%2C%20thanks%20to%20climate%20change%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Khenrab.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20these%20threats%20and%2020%20years%20on%20the%20job%2C%20his%20passion%20for%20snow%20leopards%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20waned.%20%E2%80%9CMy%20objective%20is%20to%20create%20a%20safe%20habitat%20for%20them.%20There%20is%20no%20one%20to%20represent%20the%20snow%20leopards.%20I%20like%20to%20believe%20I%20represent%20them.%20They%20are%20critical%20for%20the%20maintenance%20of%20the%20ecological%20balance.%20We%20must%20do%20everything%20to%20protect%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20concludes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by